<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14515] Short read protection in presence of almost-purgeable range tombstones may cause permanent data loss</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14515</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Because read responses don&apos;t necessarily close their open RT bounds, it&apos;s possible to lose data during short read protection, if a closing bound is compacted away between two adjacent reads from a node.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13165618">CASSANDRA-14515</key>
            <summary>Short read protection in presence of almost-purgeable range tombstones may cause permanent data loss</summary>
